                        the Secretary of State, at Paris</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d723</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">723</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-06-03T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-06-03T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="723" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/6–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>, at Paris</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-03T19:00:00-04:00">June 3, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Telac1">Telac</gloss> 50. Ref para 3 <gloss target="#t_Telac1">Telac</gloss> 38 June 1. View Ethridge negative reaction immediate
                    incorporation Pal territory now administered by Jordan or extension Brit treaty
                    to this territory (ref <gloss target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 182 June 2 being
                    rptd you<note n="1" xml:id="d723fn1">As <gloss target="#t_Telac1">Telac</gloss>
                        52, June 3, 7 p. m., not printed.</note>), Dept believes desirable inform
                    Bevin US considers advisable no action be taken above two points present time.
                    You may wish make available to Bevin Ethridge’s opinions.<note n="2" xml:id="d723fn2">Secretary Acheson, in reply from Paris on June 6, stated:
                        “We communicated to Bevin today point[s] made <gloss target="#t_Telac1">Telac</gloss> 50 repeating your <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss>s to Holmes in London requesting inform Michael Wright.
                        Embassy London instructed to follow up on Wright visit Washington.”
                        (telegram <gloss target="#t_Actel1">Actel</gloss> 44, 501.BB
                        Palestine/6–649) <p>Julius C. Holmes was Counselor of Embassy in the United
                            Kingdom.</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
